Merry Christmas!!! 🎁🎄 ⭐️🙏🏻

Today was my first Christmas in Tucson, AZ and though I am quite enjoying the warm weather compared to the frigid cold temps in Iowa I have greatly missed being with my family on this special day. Looking forward to flying home to Iowa tomorrow! Needless to say, I still had a wonderful Christmas full of great music, celebration, and worship! Played for four Christmas masses this weekend including a midnight mass at Saint Francis De Sales church. I had the pleasure of collaborating with awesome people I adore - the Snook family, Dr. Jane and Julian Ackerley, and the wonderful church choir. 🤍 I am truly blessed! Merry Christmas to you all and may you have a very Happy New Year! 🎉

I feel one of the biggest problems we’re facing in our world is loneliness. Being present, engaging, and acknowledging the dignity in all life is the start to fight it. Even by starting with something as simple as asking “How are you?” and listening to what they have to say you’ve shown that you see that person, hear them, and care about them. The smallest acts of genuine kindness can making the biggest difference. 🤍

Had the honor of meeting Texas Rangers’ Mitchell Garver today in Phoenix! He’s a stand-up guy in addition to being a great ball player. We had a fun exchange of tools from our respective trades - an album of my music and a signed piano key for a pair of his signed batting gloves. Thanks again, @mgarver ! ⚾️ 

Prior to the game, my good friend @postlesydney and I had the pleasure of touring the Musical Instrument Museum in Phoenix. The collection consists of over 15,000 musical instruments from around world. There was a Steinway piano in the museum lobby and when I sat down to play a group of grade school students led by one of the curators gathered round to learn about the instrument. It was fun to participate and see the kids excited about music!

#piano #mlb #baseball #surprisestadium #springtraining #music #phoenix #pianist #harrisonsheckler #mitchellgarver #classical #instruments
